## Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: I'm using g on my home router. Do I need a commercial license?**  
A: No, personal use on your home network is free.

**Q: I'm a small business owner. Can I use g on my office router?**  
A: No, business use requires a commercial license regardless of company size.

**Q: I'm a student learning about networking. Can I use g?**  
A: Yes, personal learning and education is free.

**Q: Can I use g in my university's network lab?**  
A: Educational institutions using g in an official capacity require a commercial license. However, students using g on their personal devices for learning are covered under personal use.

**Q: I want to offer g as part of my managed services. What do I need?**  
A: You need a commercial license. Please contact us for OEM/redistribution licensing.

**Q: Can I contribute to the project?**  
A: Yes! Contributions are welcome. By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the same dual license terms.

**Q: What if I'm not sure if my use case requires a commercial license?**  
A: When in doubt, please contact us at aezi.zhu@icloud.com. We're happy to clarify.

